Central Bank of Nigeria (CBN) in statement addressed to all authorized dealers, service providers and the general public with referred no TEN/FEM/PUB/FPC/001/005, dated June 09, 2021 cited on its website saying Re: appointment of Titan Trust Bank Plc as a designated bank for the collection of fees under the Nigeria Export Supervision Scheme (NESS).  The statement which was endorsed by Dr SO Nnaji, The Director, Trade & Exchange Department of CBN further said that this is to notify all authorized dealers, service providers and general public that honourable minister of finance, budget and national planning has approved the appointment of Titan Trust Bank as one of the designated banks for the collection of NESS Levy.  â€œAuthorised Dealers are therefore enjoined to bring the information to the attention of their exporting customers.